## Non-Functional Requirements

### NFR-1: Performance
- Process at least 10,000 records per minute
- Memory usage should not exceed 2GB for datasets up to 1M records
- Batch size configurable for different environments

### NFR-2: Reliability
- Handle network interruptions gracefully
- Retry transient failures automatically
- Maintain data consistency (no partial updates)

### NFR-3: Observability
- Log all significant events
- Provide progress indicators
- Track detailed statistics
- Log execution times

### NFR-4: Maintainability
- Use clear naming conventions
- Add JavaDoc for public methods
- Follow Spring Boot best practices
- Use Lombok to reduce boilerplate

### NFR-5: Configurability
- All MongoDB URIs configurable
- All collection names configurable
- Batch sizes configurable
- Retry settings configurable
- Log frequency configurable
